President Donald J. Trump has declared a state of emergency in the State of Texas due to the conditions resulting from Hurricane Hanna. This declaration authorizes the Department of Homeland Security, Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA), to coordinate disaster relief efforts in order to alleviate hardship and suffering caused by the emergency. FEMA is authorized to provide equipment and resources to mitigate the impacts of the emergency, with emergency protective measures being funded at 75 percent by the federal government. Jerry S. Thomas has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.